cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the design of a distributed network for white-space spectrum access, which involves issues related to networking, game theory, information theory, control systems, and multimedia. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes game-theoretic models and algorithms for channel selection and user association, which are related to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of mobility on the system performance, which is related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
